    "content_hash": "5c4a7d3b324d64f3",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About ALSO.\n\nWe’re ALSO, an electric mobility company originally conceived as a part of Rivian. We’re a passionate team of builders, dreamers, doers and innovators, focused on creating entirely new (not to mention, innovative and delightful) vertically integrated, small EVs designed to meet the global mobility challenges of today and tomorrow. Our mission is to inspire everyone to ride ALSO—replacing many local car, truck and SUV miles with ones on vehicles that are more affordable, more enjoyable and 10-50x more efficient.\n\nAs a senior Data Engineer on the ALSO backend team, you will drive technical excellence and architectural decisions with a strong focus on analytics, data modeling, and data visualization. This role sits at the intersection of engineering rigor and analytical clarity — owning how telemetry and business data are transformed into trusted, scalable, decision-ready dashboards, that will create an excellent customer experience on Also’s flagship connected EVs. You’ll lead the evolution of our connected EV platform, from secure data ingestion to product facing APIs, and influence how we build and scale at Also. You balance speed and rigor, know how to scale systems, and thrive in fast paced 0→1 environments. The systems you build will power core product features and enhance our analytics and fleet intelligence capabilities.\n\nThis is not a traditional ingestion-heavy data engineering role. You will spend the majority of your time:\n\n - Defining metrics and data quality standards\n\n - Building and owning high-impact visualizations used by leadership and product teams\n\nWhat you will do:\n\n - Design multi-level visualization experiences (exec → operational → deep-dive) and translate complex telemetry and business data into clear, intuitive visuals\n\n - Define visualization standards: metric definitions, charting patterns, UX clarity and Own dashboards as long-lived products, not one-off reports\n\n - Design and maintain analytics-layer data models (facts, dimensions, wide tables, semantic layers), Build performant datasets optimized for BI tools and large-scale querying\n\n - Partner with upstream engineers to shape event and telemetry schemas for downstream analytics, Optimize queries, storage, and compute for scale and cost efficiency in AWS\n\n - Define and enforce metric contracts across teams and Implement automated data quality checks (completeness, freshness, correctness)\n\n - Design pre- and post-pipeline validation frameworks and reduce metric drift and dashboard inconsistencies\n\n - Work cross functionally and turn ambiguous business questions into concrete metrics and dashboards\n\n - Influence without authority across multiple teams\n   \n\nWhat you will bring:\n\n - 8+ years of experience in data engineering, analytics engineering, or analytics-focused roles with proven experience owning end-to-end analytics and visualization systems\n\n - Strong background working with large-scale telemetry and business data\n\n - Deep SQL expertise and strong Python (data pipelines, transformations, automation), dbt or equivalent analytics transformation frameworks\n\n - Track record of improving data quality, metric reliability, and dashboard usability\n\n - AWS (S3, Glue, Athena, Redshift / Redshift Serverless, Lambda, EventBridge)\n\n - Databricks / Spark-based ecosystems\n\n - Orchestration tools (Airflow, MWAA, Step Functions, or similar)\n\n - Tableau, Power BI, Looker / Looker Studio (or equivalent) and experience building executive and self-serve dashboards\n\n - Strong opinions on visualization UX and metric storytelling\n\n - Event-based data models. Funnel, cohort, and time-series analysis High-volume, high-cardinality datasets\n   \n\n\nNICE TO HAVE\n\n - Experience at large-scale tech companies or data-intensive environments\n\n - Exposure to ML pipelines and feature instrumentation\n\n - Experience migrating or standardizing BI platforms\n\n - Front-end or advanced visualization experience (e.g., d3.js, custom visuals)\n\nThe estimated annual compensation for this position ranges from $165,000 - $200,000 per year, depending on experience and qualifications.\n\nWhy ALSO.\n\nWe’re passionate about helping the world find a better way to get there—wherever it is you’re headed.\n\nWe’re located in the heart of Silicon Valley and have brought together a world-class team from some of the biggest brands in the technology, automotive, cycling, outdoor recreation and retail spaces. \n\nTogether we’re working hands-on to imagine, design and build an entirely new solution to a global set of transportation challenges. \n\nPerks and Benefits\n\n - Robust health coverage. Excellent health, dental and vision insurance covered up to 100% by ALSO with FSA \u0026 HSA options.\n\n - One Medical membership and dedicated insurance advocates.\n\n - Rich fertility and family building benefits with Progyny.\n\n - Flexible time off. \n\n - 401(k) match.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
